The paper deals with the correspondence between chaotic iterations and artificial neural networks, specifically global recurrent multi-layer perceptrons. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the training of these networks to exhibit chaotic behavior, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the formal proof of chaos in these networks, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY).
